task.description: Base URL for API documentation.

task.label: exportJars
task.description: Determines whether the exported classpath for this project contains classes (false) or a packaged jar (true).

task.label: scalaVersion
task.description: The version of Scala used for building.

task.label: mergeManifests
task.description: merge manifests from libs, disable if libraries have bad manifests

task.label: moduleName
task.description: The name of the current module, used for dependency management.

task.label: conflictWarning
task.description: Configures warnings for conflicts in dependency management.

task.label: internalConfigurationMap
task.description: Maps configurations to the actual configuration used to define the classpath.

task.label: platformTarget
task.description: target API level as described by 'android list targets' (the ID string)

task.label: ivyLoggingLevel
task.description: The logging level for updating.

task.label: sbtPlugin
task.description: If true, enables adding sbt as a dependency and auto-generation of the plugin descriptor file.

task.label: otherResolvers
task.description: Resolvers not included in the main resolver chain, such as those in module configurations.

task.label: dexMinimizeMain
task.description: minimal-main-dex flag for dex, default false

task.label: lintIssues
task.description: Issues to detect, default: ApiDetectors

task.label: ivyValidate
task.description: Enables/disables Ivy validation of module metadata.

task.label: autogeneratedProject
task.description: If it exists, represents that the project (and name) were automaticlaly craeted, rather than user specified.

task.label: testForkedParallel
task.description: Whether forked tests should be executed in parallel

task.label: flavors
task.description: build flavor definitions, map of flavor names to settings

task.label: appConfiguration
task.description: Provides access to the launched sbt configuration, including the ScalaProvider, Launcher, and GlobalLock.

task.label: useSdkProguard
task.description: use the sdk proguard config or this plugin's; default = !using scala

task.label: publishArtifact
task.description: Enables (true) or disables (false) publishing an artifact.

task.label: artifactName
task.description: Function that produces the artifact name from its definition.

task.label: crossPaths
task.description: If true, enables cross paths, which distinguish input and output directories for cross-building.

task.label: autoApiMappings
task.description: If true, automatically manages mappings to the API doc URL.

task.label: ivyConfigurations
task.description: The defined configurations for dependency management. This may be different from the configurations for Project settings.

task.label: retrieveManagedSync
task.description: If true, enables synchronizing the dependencies retrieved to the current build by removed unneeded files.

task.label: useProguard
task.description: whether or not to run proguard, automatically true with useProguardInDebug

task.label: fileInputOptions
task.description: Options that take file input, which may invalidate the cache.

task.label: crossVersion
task.description: Configures handling of the Scala version when cross-building.

task.label: fork
task.description: If true, forks a new JVM when running. If false, runs in the same JVM as the build.

task.label: updateConfiguration
task.description: Configuration for resolving and retrieving managed dependencies.

task.label: crossTarget
task.description: Main directory for files generated by the build that are cross-built.

task.label: version
task.description: The version/revision of the current module.

task.label: extraAssetDirectories
task.description: list of additional android asset folders to include (primarily for flavors

task.label: buildDependencies
task.description: Definitive source of inter-project dependencies for compilation and dependency management. This is populated by default by the dependencies declared on Project instances, but may be modified. The main restriction is that new builds may not be introduced.

task.label: dexMaxHeap
task.description: Maximum heapsize for dex, default 1024m

task.label: resourceManaged
task.description: Default managed resource directory, used when generating resources.

task.label: resourceGenerators
task.description: List of tasks that generate resources.

task.label: sourcesInBase
task.description: If true, sources from the project's base directory are included as main sources.

task.label: apkSigningConfig
task.description: signing configuration for release builds

task.label: resourceDirectory
task.description: Default unmanaged resource directory, used for user-defined resources.

task.label: properties
task.description: Properties loaded from the project's .property files

task.label: logManager
task.description: The log manager, which creates Loggers for different contexts.

task.label: forceUpdatePeriod
task.description: Duration after which to force a full update to occur

task.label: rsOptimLevel
task.description: renderscript optimization level, default: 3

task.label: javaSource
task.description: Default Java source directory.

task.label: outputLayout
task.description: setting for defining project build output layout

task.label: debugIncludesTests
task.description: Whether instrumentation tests should be included in the debug apk

task.label: defaultConfiguration
task.description: Defines the configuration used when none is specified for a dependency in ivyXML.

task.label: dexAdditionalParams
task.description: additional params to pass to dex

task.label: dexMainClasses
task.description: list of class files that go into main-dex-list parameter for dex

task.label: classpathTypes
task.description: Artifact types that are included on the classpath.

task.label: apkbuildDebug
task.description: setting that determines whether to package debug or release, default: debug

task.label: cleanFiles
task.description: The files to recursively delete during a clean.

task.label: classDirectory
task.description: Directory for compiled classes and copied resources.

task.label: homepage
task.description: Project homepage.

task.label: initialCommands
task.description: Initial commands to execute when starting up the Scala interpreter.

task.label: taskTemporaryDirectory
task.description: Directory used for temporary files for tasks that is deleted after each task execution.

task.label: configuration
task.description: Provides the current configuration of the referencing scope.

task.label: thisProject
task.description: Provides the current project for the referencing scope.

task.label: watchingMessage
task.description: The message to show when triggered execution waits for sources to change.

task.label: managedResourceDirectories
task.description: List of managed resource directories.

task.label: managedSourceDirectories
task.description: Managed source directories, which contain sources generated by the build.

task.label: developers
task.description: List of developers implicated in the project

task.label: target
task.description: Main directory for files generated by the build.

task.label: javaHome
task.description: Selects the Java installation used for compiling and forking. If None, uses the Java installation running the build.

task.label: evictionWarningOptions
task.description: Options on eviction warnings after resolving managed dependencies.

task.label: apklibArtifact
task.description: artifact object for publishing apklibs

task.label: dexMulti
task.description: multi-dex flag for dex, default false

task.label: dexShards
task.description: whether to enable dex sharding, requires v21+, debug-only

task.label: libraryDependencies
task.description: Declares managed dependencies.

task.label: checksums
task.description: The list of checksums to generate and to verify for dependencies.

task.label: transitiveAndroidWarning
task.description: warn when transitive android dependencies will be ignored, default true

task.label: apkFile
task.description: consistent file name for apk output, used for IDE integration

task.label: sourceGenerators
task.description: List of tasks that generate sources.

task.label: offline
task.description: Configures sbt to work without a network connection where possible.

task.label: pollInterval
task.description: Interval between checks for modified sources by the continuous execution command.

task.label: artifact
task.description: Describes an artifact.
